---
title: One-Pot Turkey & Black Bean Soup with the Works
description: This week, we’re serving a hearty, flavorful black bean soup that’s ready in just 20 minutes—and it all cooks up in one pot, making cleanup a breeze! The beans are simmered in a richly spiced broth with onion, tomato, and Southwest seasonings until the soup is thick and the beans are tender. For toppings, load up your bowl with “the works”—white cheddar cheese, smoky red pepper crema, and crushed blue corn tortilla chips. Now that’s what we call a truly SOUP-er supper.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/674e2f91f546e01c8f277420-2394ec3c.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/6750b8dc3d226fed8fd71938-en-US.pdf
author: Sara Heilman
cuisine: North America
course: main course
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/one-pot-turkey-and-black-bean-soup-6750b8dc3d226fed8fd71938
nutrition:
  calories: 840 kcal
  fat: 38 g
  saturated fat: 13 g
  carbohydrates: 67 g
  sugar: 11 g
  protein: 48 g
  fiber: 11 g
  sodium: 1800 mg
time required: 20 minutes
servings: 2
---

Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and finely dice @onion{1} until you have 3⁄4 cup
(1 1⁄2 cups for 4 servings). Drain @black beans{1} over a small #bowl{},
reserving liquid.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a large #pot over medium-high
heat. Add onion; cook, stirring, until softened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add @Southwest spice blend{1%tablespoon}; cook, stirring, until fragrant,
~{30%seconds}.

Stir in @Tex-Mex paste{1}; cook until slightly darkened in
color, ~{1%minute}.

**Once onion is softened, add @ground turkey{10%ounce} to pot;
season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and cook, breaking up
meat into pieces, until cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.
Cook through the rest of the step as instructed.**

> Ground Poultry is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.

Stir @mushroom stock concentrate{2}, beans, half the @crushed tomatoes{1},
1 cup @water{1%cup}, and 1⁄4 cup reserved bean liquid
into pot. (For 4 servings, use all the crushed tomatoes,
2 cups water, and 1⁄2 cup bean liquid.) Bring to a boil and
cook, stirring occasionally, until thickened, ~{5-8%minutes}.

> TIP: Prefer your broth a bit thicker? Simmer a little longer—or
simmer a little less if you prefer a thinner broth! You're the
chef, after all.

Taste and season with salt and pepper. Turn off heat.

Crush a few @blue corn tortilla chips{1.5%ounce}.

Divide soup between #bowls{} and top with @white cheddar cheese{1/2%cup},
@smoky red pepper crema{2%tablespoon}, and as many crushed tortilla
chips as you like. (TIP: Start with a few crushed chips and
add more as you go to keep them crunchy!) Serve with
whole tortilla chips on the side.